			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Thinking about comming back.. how much has changed?<a name="54548"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 30 04 11:55 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, one big change is the addition of instanced zones... you or your group are the only players in the whole zone, all the mobs belong to you, but you can't get outside help either.  The instanced zones are set up in mission style adventures, some with timers some without.
<br />

<br />
Armor can be upgraded now, and I do not mean replacing it with a new piece, I mean enhancing your existing armor, with augments.  They are little gems that you can insert into your armor to give a stat bonus or an effect.
<br />

<br />
There is the addition of Alternate Advancement, leveles beyond the level cap almost...  you earn xp the same way as before, but faster (at higher levels it gets easier) than normal xp.  Each time you PING (the AA ding) you get a point, and you save points to spend on stat boosts or new abilities or to enhance existing abilities.  These alternate advancements cost between 1 point and 20 points each.
<br />

<br />
Also there are things called flags now, flags allow you to access new high end zones.  Some let you access a zone before a required level (or you can level yup and enter anyhow) and some zones you can never enter unless you earn the flags.  Some of the pieces of armor you can get in the top zones are probably equivilent to the best full set of armor you ever saw pre-luclin.  They definetly make it worth your while to go to these places (how ever NOT required to enjoy the game and do well.)
<br />

<br />
Some new types of songs, but mostly just enhanced versions of old ones, depending on your level when you quit.  We are expecting/hoping for some truely new songs in the next expansion.
<br />

<br />
Also, of a lesser note to some, but something I personally love, you can change the colors of your armor now, easily and cheaply, to any color you desire.  This allows you to take a missmatched suit of good pieces of armor and make it look like a perfectly matching set, or take your armor and turn yourself into a rainbow kid.
<br />

<br />
Some new races have been added, and a new class as well (Berserkers) also disciplines have changed slightly in how they work, making them better than they were before.
<br />

<br />
Oh, and also really cool for bards is the fact that many wearable instruments have been added to the game, as well as weapons that are instruments (besides out epic).  So you can customize a lot and become really effective.
<br />

<br />
Also the addition of the bazaar was a major change that came with the luclin expansion.  No more getting spammed in East commons and wondering if you are getting ripped off.  There is a gathering place called the bazaar, where players can turn themselves into merchants that you can right click on and buy from while they are afk, just like npc merchants.  Plus you can use the scripts that are built in to serch for gear by class, piece, stats, etc etc, and compare prices and stuff, and get the best deals available at any given time.  It makes getting new gear SOOOOOOOO much easier, and also makes selling stuff equally easy.  You can make money and get upgrades in a snap now.
<br />

<br />
I find it much more exciting now than before because there are so many more options and ways to enhance your character, and personalize it.  (and I know i have forgotten some things that people probably consider major, but those are the ones I can think of right this minute)
<br />

<br />
And I would like to extend you a warm welcome back... if you do decide to come back.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
