			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Thinking about comming back.. how much has changed?<a name="54573"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 31 04 8:51 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Bards are over powered until the very very very top now (as in, huge gigaraids required to take down trash mobs) <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Oh, and some thing you should really be aware of about AA's, you can get yourself to sow speed 100% of the time period with them, can increase unbuffed hp by 12%, and do all sorts of amazing things.
<br />

<br />
Fading Memories is basically like a bard feign death.  900 mana but you can still move, big problem is that it is only regular invis that keeps things from re-agroing (ie, named, undead, etc. will see through and reagro).
<br />

<br />
About raiding, they've made it a lot easier.  Now it's sort of like a giant group (72 max people in a raid, many things require you to have less then 72 people, GoD for example).  You even get a new text channel - raidspeak.
<br />

<br />
They revamped a bunch of zones.  I'm not sure if you'd ever actually been in any of them, except maybe Plane of Hate.
<br />

<br />
Oh, and they added a new inventory slot.  It's called a 'charm.'  It sort of scales with a prerequisite.  IE, one charm will have better stats if you're in an illusion, another has better stats the more money you carry, etc.  
<br />

<br />
Also, because of the bazaar, eeevil farmers, (and partially due to instanced zones), inflation is THROUGH THE ROOF!  1k is NOT very much money right now.  I'd say the equivilent of 1k from a few years ago is something around 15-20k.  Maybe more.
<br />

<br />
One last thing, with the expansion &quot;Lost Dungeons of Norrath&quot; you can buy some REALLY nice armor by doing 'adventures.'  Basically, they give you a mission.  You have 90 minutes to complete it.  At level 65, you get 51 'adventure points' for a normal adventure and 105 for a 'high risk' (which is aptly named, the trash mobs hit for up to 998!).  You get less the lower level you are, but can do an adventure with 3 - 6 (including yourself) people starting at level 20.  You save up and use these points to 'buy' equipment from special merchants.  For example, with a bunch of adventuring, you could easily have a breastplate with 20 stamina (well, 19 if you don't do hards at 65), 69 ac, 11 charisma, 11 wis and int, 12 to 3 different saves, 100 mana (yes, mana is important now for bards!), 140 hit points, flowing thought 2, 11 charisma, and probably a bit more that I don't remember.
<br />

<br />
Which reminds me.  They changed a bunch of worn stuff on items.  Flowing thought is now called 'Mana Regeneration +#', hp regen is the same - mana, they give the % of haste on all worn haste items, and now have worn DS's.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Also, roleplaying aspects have died out a lot...  It is NOT the same game any more.  It is still fun though<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />.
<br />

<br />

<br />
One really big thing to mention is that computer needs have changed a lot.  You may want to look at minimum requirements...</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
